  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6500.41 sitting right on the massive -9080M negative gamma wall, dealers are aggressively buying the breakout above 6500 which is creating the violent upside momentum (26% surge in 1-min). The breakout regime with heavy negative gamma concentration means dealers will continue buying any dips back toward 6490-6500 and accelerate purchases if we push higher, creating a feedback loop that should drive continuation toward the 6505 positive gamma ceiling where they'll flip to selling pressure. Watch for either explosive continuation through 6505 (if that positive gamma gets overwhelmed) or a sharp reversal/chop between 6500-6505 as dealers oscillate between buying and selling flows.",
